Previously, to change just a sprite's alpha I had to do this:

``` java
Color color = sprite.getColor();
color.a = newAlpha;
sprite.setColor(color);
```

now you can just do this, and it should perform a little faster as well (not tested):

``` java
sprite.setAlpha(newAlpha);
```

Hi,

the implementation of method overlaps in Circle is broken. It works well only when circles have the same radius. 

Current implementation: 

```
/** @param c the other {@link Circle}
 * @return whether this circle overlaps the other circle. */
public boolean overlaps (Circle c) {
    float dx = x - c.x;
    float dy = y - c.y;
    float distance = dx * dx + dy * dy;
    float radiusSum = radius + c.radius;
    return distance < radiusSum * radiusSum;
}
```

You need to change first two lines to: 
        float dx = x - c.x + radius - c.radius;
        float dy = y - c.y + radius - c.radius;

